// compiler/codegen/nvptx_p10_matmul_test.hexa
// RFC 071 P5++ — source-to-silicon matmul fixture
//
// @version 0.0.1
// @capabilities [pure]
// @phase("parse_only")
//
// This file is the SOURCE-LEVEL fixture for F-RFC071-NVPTX-MATMUL-
// SOURCE-TO-SILICON. It exercises the `gpu_matmul` builtin synthesis
// path landed in `compiler/lower/hir_to_mir.hexa` (call-branch
// intercept that emits the synthetic STMT_LOAD + STMT_LOAD + STMT_BINOP
// ("matmul") + STMT_STORE shape).
//
// Sister to `nvptx_p3_source_to_silicon_test.hexa` (RFC 071 P3,
// vec-add lane). Where P3 closes the source-to-silicon path for
// element-wise kernels via the generic MIR-walk codegen, this P10
// fixture closes the matmul tier via the synthetic-MIR shape
// recogniser (NVPTX `_nvptx_mfunc_is_matmul_shape`, ROCm
// `_rocm_mfunc_is_matmul_shape`, Metal `_metal_mfunc_is_matmul_shape`).
//
// Kernel signature — `(a, b, c, M, N, K)` — matches the codegen's
// hardcoded 6-`u64` `.param` bank (`<name>_param_0..5`); see the
// `_nvptx_emit_matmul_param_bank` helper. The signature order is
// load-bearing because the codegen reads dims from
// `ld.param.u64 %rd3..5` directly.
//
// Body — a single `gpu_matmul(c, a, b, M, N, K)` call. The HIR→MIR
// synthesis intercepts at `callee_text == "gpu_matmul"` and emits
// the 4-stmt skeleton:
//   STMT_LOAD   matmul_va ← a
//   STMT_LOAD   matmul_vb ← b
//   STMT_BINOP  matmul_vc = matmul_va matmul matmul_vb
//   STMT_STORE  c ← matmul_vc
// followed by the implicit STMT_RETURN appended in `_lower_fn`. The
// codegen recogniser tolerates the trailing return (`len(stmts) >= 4`
// + positional kind/op checks on stmts[0..3]).
//
// HONEST SCOPE (@D g3):
//   * `hexa parse` rc=0 expected on this fixture (parse-gate).
//   * HIR→MIR synthesis lands this cycle.
//   * Silicon-fire is BLOCKED on this worktree because the N86 NVPTX
//     matmul codegen (3 shape recognisers + 3 PTX emit-body functions
//     + dispatcher) is missing — it was reverted from main by N88
//     (commit e9c89904, 424-line silent file-drop; the documented
//     `feedback_worktree_merge_silent_filedrop` pattern). The
//     parallel N99 worktree is the recovery lane.
//   * Once the N86 codegen is restored, the PTX emit substring
//     contract is: `.visible .entry matmul_kernel` + `wmma.load.a` +
//     `wmma.load.b` + `wmma.mma` + `wmma.store.d`. SASS-level
//     verification + numerical equivalence vs CPU FP32 reference is
//     the silicon-fire side of F-RFC071-NVPTX-MATMUL-SOURCE-TO-SILICON.

// ── The kernel (gpu/SPEC.md §2 — @gpu_kernel must return void) ───────

@gpu_kernel
fn matmul_kernel(a: [f16], b: [f16], c: [f32], M: i32, N: i32, K: i32) {
    gpu_matmul(c, a, b, M, N, K)
}
